            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> Manius Bassi<lb break="no" n="3"/>anus vixit an<lb break="no" n="4"/><expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> LXII <expan><abbr>bul</abbr><ex>euta</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>His</abbr><ex>triae</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/>Manius Vitales <note>sic</note> ne<lb break="no" n="6"/>pos eius vixit an<lb break="no" n="7"/><expan><abbr>ni</abbr><ex>s</ex></expan> VIIII <supplied reason="lost">Vitalia</supplied><lb break="no" n="8"/>nus Bassianus <lb n="9"/><expan><abbr>fil</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> eius et Scapul<lb break="no" n="10"/>lia Gemella con<expan><ex>i</ex><abbr>unx</abbr></expan> <lb n="11"/>eius <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ibi</ex></expan> et <surplus>et sibi</surplus> paren<lb break="no" n="12"/>tibus bene meritis <lb n="13"/>posuerunt <lb n="14"/>have viator
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>2 nicht aneinanderpassende Fragmente erhalten; Maße beziehen sich auf Fragment a; Maße Fragment b: (112) x 94 x 24. Oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes Totenmahlrelief. Hederae. CIL III 7527: nur das untere Fragment. CIL III 14449: nur das obere Fragment. (B): Conrad; IScM I: Z. 11: s(ibi) et {sibi}; Z. 12: bene merentis.</p>
            </div>
